(13) Person
means any individual, corporation, partnership, limited liability company,
association, or voluntary organization;

(iv) The state in which the executive or management committee of the
board of directors or similar governing person or persons of the entity conducts
the majority of its meetings;

(16) Receivership court
means the court in the insolvent or impaired insurer's state having jurisdiction
over the conservation, rehabilitation, or liquidation of the insurer;

(18) State means a state,
the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, and any United States possession, territory,
